caption: Great food, amazing cocktails. I'm a big fan of their cheeseburger. Good covid precautions.
Great service with an interesting menu

Watermelon daiquiri was more like a martini. Sweet potato tacos were deep fried. Cauliflower bites not spicy at all. Chicken sandwich was huge. Service was great. Food ok. Very limited menu.  Nice outdoor patio.
My husband and our two boys enjoyed the smash burger. I enjoyed the chicken sandwich. Definitely will be going back and telling our friends and family to go there to eat!
Hip hop and old School DJ on Fridays. GREAT vibes. Food was awesome and there were great veggie options. Great experience.
I really liked this place. Comfortable and cute environment. The food was very tasty. Good beer selection. And our service was great. I will definitely come here again.
Great food, good service and a very warm atmosphere.
Great selection of unique drinks.  Friendly and attentive staff.  Solid food.  5 stars.
Great burger. Decent selection of local beers. Great locstion.
Delicious cocktails and amazing food. I always get the shrimp po boy when I come here, never left disappointed
Great brunch
Food and beverages are GREAT! Service is exceptional. Beth is amongst the best bartenders I have ever experienced!

Stopped in for brunch on a Sunday afternoon. It wasn’t too crowded which appealed to us. I used to come and eat here when it was Dunlay’s. I was pleasantly surprised to see so many TVs on the walls. It gave the place a little bit of a sports bar vibe (which in Logan is not everyone’s favorite) but was fine for me since I like sports. There were football games playing on there. Brunch menu had lots of options for food and cocktails. It all sounded very good. We shared the lox, huevos, and smash burger with some mimosas to wash it all down. Everything was very tasty and our server and the rest of the staff were all very friendly.

Passable food. Horrible service. went for brunch, place was nearly empty - waited for 15 mins before anyone came to our table. Waited a long time for them to take the order. Waited a long time to get the check. Waited a long time for them to process the check.
Bloody Mary and avocado toast were so so good. Server Nicole couldn’t have been friendlier and quick. Totally returning.

Went for a brunch meeting and the service matched their food. It was difficult to choose between the items because they all sounded great. I am only giving 4 stars because I didn't pay for anything so, I am not sure what the cost of what I had would've been to properly give an accurate rating. Definitely will be back to try again.
Immemorable Everytime but whatever. Watch out for judging runners

Open layout with sidewalk seating adjacent to the square makes this a great spot during warmer months. Very friendly staff execute a straightforward but well-rounded menu that combines elements of classic pub fare with fresh contemporary twists. It fits the neighborhood and, last but not least, does so at a reasonable price.

We’ve waited to try Merchant as we’ve been mourning the loss of Dunlays... still mourning. The cauliflower app was great, gave us high hopes for the rest of our meal. But the pasta and shrimp po-boy were underwhelming.  Will say it’s a decent place to watch a game, TVs on all sides.

A friend of a friend picked this place for our group. I would say that it is mediocre at best. We tried a bunch of dishes: tacos de papas (dry and flavorless), shishito peppers (I've had much better in this town), cheddar biscuits (ok with "honey" butter), carrots (decent). The cauliflower was really the only thing worth eating and mentioning. It's the only dish I can recommend. Happily, I was impressed by the service. We were told the drinks were awesome and I would beg to differ. Again, just mediocre. With all the fab restaurants in town,  what a disappointment.

Excellent neighborhood eatery.  Not a large menu, and that’s a good thing because what they do serve features fresh ingredients and hand-crafted care. Still, the menu is carefully planned to appeal to a broad range of culinary persuasions. Thumbs up to The Nashville and Barbacoa Tacos.  Service was friendly, attentive and efficient. Reasonably priced. A great value.
Good food and friendly service; brunch portions are small

Great Logan square location for site seeing. Food is pretty good. The wings are good plain, nice crunch, skip the sauce or get on the side. Burgers and chips (with home made onion dip) are great and of course the cocktails. 4 stars for food. Will go back. Service gave them 5 stars.

Merchant is always a solid brunch choice. I usually get the Huevos (eggs, chorizo, Masa cakes, Verde sauce) and it never disappoints. If you can get a spot outside in the summer there's some good people (and dog) watching too

First time visiting tonight, placed a pick-up order. They were very generous and accommodating!! The service really made my night. & the salad that I ordered, the kale salad with granny apples and pecans, was simple but sooooo delicious and satisfying. The ingredients were very fresh. I loved it and ate every bite!
Cheeseburger and fries! Delicious.
Fantastic decor and vibe. Food was actually quite good, but the service stole the show. Huge shout out to Remedy for making us feel right at home.
Get. The. Freaking. Biscuits.  Service is good, too.

I don’t get the theme of this place but it seemed kind of slap shod and thrown together. The menu was all over the place but the food was really good. Also, we went in and sat down and were ignored for twenty minutes the second time we stopped in so we just left. They need to be more attentive. It wasn’t even busy.
Good sammich

Nice summer venue with open glass doors looking out at sidewalk tables and a park directly across the street. We could see a couple stringing a hammock up across the street while walkers and strollers captured the sidewalk in front of us. It has a beautiful view, trendy mixed  drinks (30 pictures) , and craft beers. The bathrooms were clean . The service was friendly. The drinks were deemed excellent by the group.
Great place excellent service!
Waited more than an hour for our food. Very slow service.
Decent food and good kids menu and great patio facing the square. That's about it. Service was really slow, polite and cordial, just slow.
Tacos were very good!
Totally works
Good food and nice atmosphere
Ridiculously expensive.
Great food! ♥️
Great Service, great bartenders.

Love this place, my wife and I come almost every Sunday for Brunch.  The owner is usually around and has twice comped our food or drinks bc the speed or quality wasn’t to his standard. Neither time did we complain or ask for this he just swung by the table said he noticed xyz and wanted to take care of it for us.  The food is great and creative. So are the drinks. Great spot that you can usually get in without more than a 15 minute wait.
Delicious food and Bloody Mary's
A bunch of us met here after a pro-wrestling show at Logan Square Auditorium. It's a bar. Staff seemed cool.

Came here late in the evening on Sunday night. Place was pretty empty. Place has a cute feel and look. Service was prompt. My friend arrived early and had an order of elote fritters ready and waiting, which were quite tasty. For dinner I ordered the barbacoa tacos, which was  an order of three tacos of corn tortilla with brisket, onion and cilantro. The taco had a slight kick if heat. Overall the tacos weren't the best I've ever had, but still tasty. I also ordered the cauliflower small plate with was dressed with vegan sweet and sour sauce. These were really good. My only critique was they added a bit too much sauce. There was a pool of it at the bottom of the bowl. My friend ordered the Smash Burger which really seemed to enjoy cause she devoured it, haha. Overall the place had a good atmosphere and tasty food. Would definitely visit again.
Amazing place!! The chicken sandwich and the smash Burger are mouth watering good.

Brunch, lunch, dinner, or drinks - I love visiting Merchant! They serve up quality dishes with great service. This is one of my go-to spots!  Some of my favorites are the tasty potatoes, deluxe burger, and you cant go wrong with the small plates. Be sure to ask about their specials - they always have amazing options!!
Beet salad was delicious.
Brunch is delish! Get the burrito-you won't be disappointed.
Great brunch menu.
Delicious food and great atmosphere
Customers were very racist and staff did nothing to ease confrontation.
I cannot recommend Merchant enough! I've been for lunch and late night, everything on the menu is delicious and great variety of beers and cocktails, something for everyone! I can't wait to go back!
I actually had a list of reviews and meant to give you guys a 5, that Nashville Hot is worth it alone. Thanks for the reply though!

Thanks Mave for the great service. I really enjoyed the tacos, but was confused by the elote fritters. I like the concept, but the lack of a unifying theme made it confusing as a first timer. Great beer selection with even better background music.

I have been here three times for brunch and dinner. The cocktails are delicious, inventive and fairly priced. The brunch burrito is amazingly delicious. The space is large, open and slightly loud - a good place for kids. Service has generally been fast and courteous though one day our server was also the bartender, which made her a little slow. My biggest issue is the cauliflower. This is clearly their vegetarian "buffalo wings" option. For a price point of $11 for cauliflower I was expecting something pretty magical and that was not delivered. The portion was the size of a dinner side and had no flavor until hot sauce was added. A $4 or $5 price point would be more appropriate.
Awesome brunch!

Cool atmosphere, nice selection of beers, and great food. Burger was super tasty and came with a ketchup and mayo dipping sauce that was to die for! Nice fries too! Another great addition to the Logan Square food scene
Great food
Discovered this place that was just around the corner from Lula cafe.  Brunch was really tasty at a good price.  Will definitely go back!
great place and food!-only thing i could recommend is work on ice-t and the water...not from the gun:)
Good food , great beer, wonderful staff
Awesome happy hour food and drink specials from 3-6! Great ambiance and really friendly service.
Love the menu and atmosphere.
The food is phenomenal. The fried rice arancini is superb, and the smash burger is what every burger aspires to be.
Incredible drink menu with a wide variety of choices. The pisco sour was amazing. The food is unique and delicious, especially the burger. Solid place to spend time and be with your friends.
Good food, nice ambient. Friendly service
Spicy Paloma hands down best cocktail. ELOTE fritters are my new jam & jelly
Innovative and approachable, always delicious. Chef Matthew Skolarus is seriously bringing the heat!!
Great food. Good spin on classic cocktails.

Great location. Found parking right away around the corner. Good atmosphere and great service. I had the wings Wich had a lemon and garlic flavor. Best wings I've had recently. And the Smash burger was just delicious. Very juicy and cooked to perfection. Definitely recommend this place. Will go again.
Smashburger melts in your mouth!!  Amazing cocktails, and everyone is super friendly!

Went here on a Sunday around 12pm. Plenty of seating available. Friendly staff. Nice atmosphere. But then there is the burger. The meat fell apart and it was covered in way too much cheese. Nothing else to top it but sauce (which was good) and a bun. Both myself and my girlfriend didn’t finish them. The sever came by and asked to see if we were okay because they had noticed we didn’t eat much. They took the burgers away and gave us 20% off on the bill (having worked in the industry, comping one would have been more appropriate). While paying the check I noticed another lady that had ordered the burger, with an upset look on her face, scraping off a good amount of the cheese before taking a bite. We didn’t try anything else, but based on the burger, I’m apprehensive on the menu. If you’re looking for a great burger in Chicago, this one needs a lot of work to even get an “honorable mention.”

We had a lovely time at Merchant! It’s new to the neighborhood and a lovely addition. We order the burger to split (why split?!!) and an asparagus salad. The asparagus salad was awesome - in think there were beets in it?! Will definitely visit again! Hope these guys do well!
This place is the god damn bee’s knees.  Friendly staff, playful menu, seriously good bites.  Would definitely recommend!!!

Very sad to see Dunlays go.  Merchant has potential to be a solid replacement.  Drinks:  Beer list was good, full of the plenty of locals.  The cocktail list was full of "spin on a classic" cocktails.  The spicy Paloma was fantastic.  The whole table switched to this for the second round.  Appetisers:  The chicken wings are giant lightly breaded and fried crispy.  The 75' sauce is a light slightly sour ginger lemongrassy coating.  The wings came practically naked and needed to be tossed.  I would like a slightly thicker sauce or more of it.  The elotes fritters were fantastic.  Tasted like authentic esquites in fried fritter form.  The app that we were most excited for was the fried rice arancini on a bed of homemade kimchi.  It was great.  Had a nice slight fish sauce funk to it that went perfect with the sweet/sour/spicy dipping sauce.  I would like a bit more spicy, but the balls were great.  Main courses:  We opted to share the large size entrees, overall they were really really good.  We saved the "handhelds" for next time.  4 of us shared the raviolo, the salmon, and the grilled octopus.  This was a good amount of food with the apps.  Starting with the raviolo.  I am not misspelling it, it is a singlular ravioli, filled with homemade queso fresco and runny egg.  The plate is covered in the corn and chorizo flavored ground sausage.  The raviolo was good, but the grilled corn and sausage was really the Star of the dish.  I think it could be improved as a gnocchi or multiple mini ravioli.  The grilled octopus was perfect, I wouldn't change anything on it.  Spicy baslmic glaze with onions and red peppers, great dish.  The salmon was a dark horse dish.  I wasn't super excited about it from menu description, but they executed it flawlessly.  Large piece of salmon cooked perfectly medium rare with a super crispy skin served on a bed of mouth watering grilled leeks.  Would eat again for sure.  The waitress said those leeks will also be part of a feta omlet when they start doing brunch.  They have a kids menu, but none printed yet.  The chicken tenders were so fantastic I told the chef they need to be an entree.  Panko breaded chicken thighs served with the sweet/sour/spicy sauce and fries.  We had a side of fries, double fried with a side of what seemed to be catsup aioli.  Nice and salty, very crispy.  Service staff made a few small mistakes, but nothing a bit more experience will solve. I think once they get a bit more familiar with the menu and the flow, this will be as fantastic addition to the neighborhood.  If they make the chicken tenders a regular menu item, I will go back just for them.  Bathroom has changing table.

Amazing experience! Staff is extremely friendly and I’m obsessed with the menu! It’s different and I crave the smashburger now. The raviolo is one of my favorite dishes too. Such an inviting atmosphere - from the music, staff, outdoor patio and lighting. I’ll defnitely be back!

Love the cocktails and food here! They have so many vegetarian options and everything is cooked to perfection. Service was friendly and attentive. So excited bout Merchant as an addition to Logan Square! Welcome to the neighborhood.

Merchant is perfect for any time of day or night! The cocktails are amazing and the Elote Fritters and Eggplant Meatballs are musts!! I can’t wait to go back. Definitely recommend for anyone heading to the Logan Square area.
Great cocktails, fast service, interesting menu. Good to see a fresh vibe in the square! Sure to satifsy the suburban yuppie and struggling artist alike.
